Compiled DSP programs inherit the parent program‚Äôs structure

This is unique and important: a tiny model can‚Äôt memorize all facts or reliably control e2e execution‚Äîeven large models ‚Äúself-distract‚Äù*!

But compiler *can* teach it to generate search queries or answer Qs w/ context!

In the compiled program, DSP's runtime intercepts generation and forwards it to a tiny LM that the compiler has fine-tuned for the transformations.

We do this for multi-hop search: our program uses only six question-answer pairs, *zero* multi-hop queries, 800 unlabeled questions

Further, the curators signal $GRT on subgraphs to indicate the subgraphs that are to be indexed.

The network aims to reward the indexers that stake $GRT in the marketplace through query fees for indexing services and sending queries to #subgraphs.

‚è©GRT Creation & Staking:

In the #Graph network, contributors such as the indexers, delegators, & curators need to stake $GRT to participate. 

Accordingly, indexers stake $GRT to supply services in the query market, and delegators delegate GRT to indexers.

‚è©Security of @graphprotocol:

The Graph Network is secured with the use of #Ethereum archive nodes and node operators like Infura or #Alchemy. 

Analytics companies can build applications to query subgraph data that is indexed by The Graph.

‚è©Introducing @graphprotocol:

It is the indexing protocol for data networks like #Ethereum and IPFS! 

The #Graph allows developers to build and publish open APIs, called subgraphs, that applications can query with GraphQL to retrieve #blockchain data.

When to use

1. Use when performing intermediate calculations or calculations that are used multiple times within a single query

2. Use as a substitute in complex queries with multiple levels of nested subqueries

In general, using CTEs makes code easier to understand and debug
3. Simplicity: CTEs allow one to write complex queries using a readable syntax

Benefits to using CTEs:

1. Readability: CTEs make complex SQL queries more readable by breaking them down into smaller, more manageable parts.

2. Reusability: CTEs can be referenced multiple times within a single query, making it easier to reuse

Example Demo:

The CTE example "sales_cte" calculates the total sales made by each salesperson.

The main query selects only salespersons who made more than or equal to 1000 in total_sales https://t.co/RF1gMqnqZy

Points to note:
1. A CTE result can be referenced within a SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, or DELETE statement

2. Result of  CTE is not stored permanently. Only lasts for the duration of the query

3. CTEs can be referred to as named subquery

4. CTEs can be created within another CTE
